    <element id="ServiceRequest">
      <path value="ServiceRequest" />
      <short value="NursingIntervention" />
      <comment value="The zib NursingIntervention defines the concepts to describe nursing interventions across several use cases:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;* as a singular event that has been performed&#xD;&#xA;* as a singular event that is planned or requested&#xD;&#xA;* as a repeating series of events that is planned, requested, or has been (partially) performed&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;However, in its current version, the zib only recognizes that these use cases exist and doesn't provide definitions on how to apply its data model to these different use cases. Nor does it specify a relation between instances of performed interventions and (series of) planned interventions. &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Since FHIR-resources are assumed to describe either an event or a request, the interpretation of the zib in the context of FHIR is not straightforward. In [ZIB-2431](https://nictiz.atlassian.net/issues/ZIB-2431), a proposal in the interpretation of the interpretation of the different zib concepts in these different contexts is made. As a result, two different profiles are defined for zib NursingIntervention:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;* A profile on Procedure ([zib-NursingIntervention-event](http://nictiz.nl/fhir/StructureDefinition/zib-NursingIntervention-event)) to register singular nursing interventions that are performed (or are to be performed).&#xD;&#xA;* The current profile on ServiceRequest (zib-NursingIntervention-request) to register planned and requested singular nursing interventions, and to describe series of nursing interventions.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;In the ZIB ticket mentioned above, it has been recognized that not all concepts from the zib are applicable for every use case. For this reason, the following zib concepts are not represented in the current event profile:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;*" />
